INSERT INTO `TABLE_PREFIXhelp` (`id`,`title`,`text_markdown`,`text_html`,`rank`,`access`,`status`) VALUES (1,'Searching a table','Click the **Search** navigation link to view/hide search options for that table.\r\n\r\nYou will typically be presented with several search options of the following types:\r\n\r\n- Order by: Select from available options to order search results, and click \"DESC\" checkbox to reverse search order.\r\n- Text input: Leave blank to ignore or enter any text that you wish to match that column.(NB: the search engine will look for all text that contains the characters you entered, so if you enter \"ark\" that will match \"dark\" park\" \"market\" etc. If you want an exact match then put an \"=\" sign before text\r\n- Number input: Only valid numbers and decimal separator if applicable. NB: you can use \"<, >, <>\" operators before entered number to designate less than, greater than, not equal to.\r\n- Select lists: Leave as default \"All\" to ignore, or select a specific value from list for an exact match\r\n- Dates : Click the \"From\" and \"To\" check-boxes to activate search from and to entered dates. NB: you can enter date text directly or select from calendar which automatically appears when you select date fields\r\n \r\nOnce you are happy with entered search terms, click the Search button to view first 100 results in standard list view. You can use  \">>>\" navigation links to step through  all results.\r\n\r\nFinally you can download search results to a csv/excel file using the link provided at top of results page. NB: the default \"csv/excel\" link only includes visible data, while the \"All\" option includes all row data available from edit /view links.\r\n','<p>Click the <strong>Search</strong> navigation link to view/hide search options for that table.</p>\n<p>You will typically be presented with several search options of the following types:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Order by: Select from available options to order search results, and click &quot;DESC&quot; checkbox to reverse search order.</li>\n<li>Text input: Leave blank to ignore or enter any text that you wish to match that column.(NB: the search engine will look for all text that contains the characters you entered, so if you enter &quot;ark&quot; that will match &quot;dark&quot; park&quot; &quot;market&quot; etc. If you want an exact match then put an &quot;=&quot; sign before text</li>\n<li>Number input: Only valid numbers and decimal separator if applicable. NB: you can use &quot;&lt;, &gt;, &lt;&gt;&quot; operators before entered number to designate less than, greater than, not equal to.</li>\n<li>Select lists: Leave as default &quot;All&quot; to ignore, or select a specific value from list for an exact match</li>\n<li>Dates : Click the &quot;From&quot; and &quot;To&quot; check-boxes to activate search from and to entered dates. NB: you can enter date text directly or select from calendar which automatically appears when you select date fields</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are happy with entered search terms, click the Search button to view first 100 results in standard list view. You can use  &quot;&gt;&gt;&gt;&quot; navigation links to step through  all results.</p>\n<p>Finally you can download search results to a csv/excel file using the link provided at top of results page. NB: the default &quot;csv/excel&quot; link only includes visible data, while the &quot;All&quot; option includes all row data available from edit /view links.</p>',20,'USER','OK'),(2,'Standard page user interface','Most pages in the portal have a default table list view with a set of list navigation links at the top and row specific links within the table rows.\r\n\r\nThe table navigation links are as follows:\r\n\r\n- List all .... : Click this to view first 100 rows in table sorted by the default\r\n- Info : Cick this to view/hide table specific info\r\n- Search : Click this to view/hide search options\r\n- Add a new ... : Click this to add a new row to table\r\n\r\n\r\nWithin each table row their are the following links:\r\n\r\n- Edit : Click to view/edit the row data\r\n- View : Click to view row data\r\n- Delete: Click to delete row from table\r\n\r\n**NB1:** Typically, due to space constraints, not all row data is displayed. Click Edit or view links to display all available data for row.\r\n\r\n**NB2:** If you receive an error message when adding or updating a row in the table, then none of the row data has been updated. Please fix error and click submit button again','<p>Most pages in the portal have a default table list view with a set of list navigation links at the top and row specific links within the table rows.</p>\n<p>The table navigation links are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>List all .... : Click this to view first 100 rows in table sorted by the default</li>\n<li>Info : Cick this to view/hide table specific info</li>\n<li>Search : Click this to view/hide search options</li>\n<li>Add a new ... : Click this to add a new row to table</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Within each table row their are the following links:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Edit : Click to view/edit the row data</li>\n<li>View : Click to view row data</li>\n<li>Delete: Click to delete row from table</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>NB1:</strong> Typically, due to space constraints, not all row data is displayed. Click Edit or view links to display all available data for row.</p>\n<p><strong>NB2:</strong> If you receive an error message when adding or updating a row in the table, then none of the row data has been updated. Please fix error and click submit button again</p>',10,'USER','OK'),(3,'Document management','Often a table will contain a \"Documents\" column with a \"**Manage**\" link in each row.\r\n\r\nIf any documents have been uploaded before then the latest ones are listed in table view with links to download.\r\n\r\nTo upload documents associated with that row in table or to view all documents linked to that row, click on \"manage\" link and you will see a pop-up window.\r\n\r\nIf no documents exist for that row then the pop-up view will default to adding a new document. \r\nOnce documents exist you will see the familiar table/list view of all documents with links to edit document details or to delete document. \r\nTo download or view the document simply click on document name.\r\nClick on \"Add a new document\" link and either select the documents you wish to upload or drag and drop them into the grey area.\r\n\r\n**NB:** You still need to click \"Upload selected documents\" button to finish the process.','<p>Often a table will contain a &quot;Documents&quot; column with a &quot;<strong>Manage</strong>&quot; link in each row.</p>\n<p>If any documents have been uploaded before then the latest ones are listed in table view with links to download.</p>\n<p>To upload documents associated with that row in table or to view all documents linked to that row, click on &quot;manage&quot; link and you will see a pop-up window.</p>\n<p>If no documents exist for that row then the pop-up view will default to adding a new document.\nOnce documents exist you will see the familiar table/list view of all documents with links to edit document details or to delete document.\nTo download or view the document simply click on document name.\nClick on &quot;Add a new document&quot; link and either select the documents you wish to upload or drag and drop them into the grey area.</p>\n<p><strong>NB:</strong> You still need to click &quot;Upload selected documents&quot; button to finish the process.</p>',30,'USER','OK'),(4,'User management','System users are added from the \"**System, All users**\" menu option.\r\n\r\n**Please note:**\r\n\r\n- Users cannot register, they need to be allocated by an administrator. Once added the administrator can then send them a login link or password reset.\r\n- The user can also request a login link or password reset provided they exist as a user.\r\n- Each user has an access level which must be set accordingly. You do not want to give anybody you dont trust GOD access to the system!\r\n\r\n**Access levels:**\r\n\r\n Users are assigned an access level from following options in descending order of access:\r\n\r\n- GOD: The user can do anything in system and most importantly manage other users. Only users with this access can see \"System\" menu option.\r\n- ADMIN: The user can create, add, update delete data anywhere in system\r\n- USER: The user can create, add, update but NOT delete data\r\n- VIEW: The user can only view data without modifying it.\r\n\r\n**Menu & Help minimum  access**\r\n\r\nWhen you create menu items and help topics, you can specify the minimum access level required. So if the minimum access is ADMIN then only ADMIN and GOD access users can see that.\r\n\r\n','<p>System users are added from the &quot;<strong>System, All users</strong>&quot; menu option.</p>\n<p><strong>Please note:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Users cannot register, they need to be allocated by an administrator. Once added the administrator can then send them a login link or password reset.</li>\n<li>The user can also request a login link or password reset provided they exist as a user.</li>\n<li>Each user has an access level which must be set accordingly. You do not want to give anybody you dont trust GOD access to the system!</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Access levels:</strong></p>\n<p>Users are assigned an access level from following options in descending order of access:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>GOD: The user can do anything in system and most importantly manage other users. Only users with this access can see &quot;System&quot; menu option.</li>\n<li>ADMIN: The user can create, add, update delete data anywhere in system</li>\n<li>USER: The user can create, add, update but NOT delete data</li>\n<li>VIEW: The user can only view data without modifying it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Menu &amp; Help minimum  access</strong></p>\n<p>When you create menu items and help topics, you can specify the minimum access level required. So if the minimum access is ADMIN then only ADMIN and GOD access users can see that.</p>',40,'GOD','OK');
